WEBVTT

00:00:08.321 --> 00:00:11.491
You're resting your head on your face
and sighing like a girl who's in love.

00:00:11.574 --> 00:00:13.910
- Was I doing that?
- Yes, you were.

00:00:14.661 --> 00:00:15.662
Don't tell me

00:00:15.745 --> 00:00:18.498
there's been some development
with your ex-boyfriend.

00:00:19.833 --> 00:00:20.917
Well…

00:00:21.793 --> 00:00:23.920
I couldn't stop myself from saying…

00:00:24.003 --> 00:00:28.007
I'm sorry. I'm starting to like you again.

00:00:28.591 --> 00:00:31.261
Maybe I shouldn't have made a move?

00:00:31.344 --> 00:00:32.178
I see.

00:00:32.262 --> 00:00:35.682
So that's why you're eagerly
waiting for a reply, right?

00:00:44.816 --> 00:00:47.277
TAIGA: CAN I CALL YOU SOMETIME TODAY?

00:00:49.529 --> 00:00:50.780
I see.

00:00:51.656 --> 00:00:53.533
You made up with your girlfriend, huh?

00:00:54.409 --> 00:00:55.493
Yeah.

00:00:56.119 --> 00:00:59.122
So, regarding what you said the other day…

00:00:59.831 --> 00:01:00.915
I'm sorry…

00:01:02.333 --> 00:01:03.459
Okay.

00:01:04.752 --> 00:01:08.756
I was happy
that I won your approval, though.

00:01:12.552 --> 00:01:14.262
If this is the end,

00:01:14.345 --> 00:01:16.681
can't we have this conversation in person?

00:01:17.974 --> 00:01:21.186
Sorry, but I don't want to cause
my girlfriend any misunderstandings.

00:01:22.312 --> 00:01:24.564
You just dumped me,
so stop flaunting it in my face.

00:01:26.608 --> 00:01:27.609
But…

00:01:28.359 --> 00:01:29.402
I'm happy

00:01:30.194 --> 00:01:33.114
that you were able to keep
this precious girlfriend of yours.

00:01:34.240 --> 00:01:35.116
Yeah.

00:01:35.700 --> 00:01:37.035
Thanks for everything.

00:01:37.827 --> 00:01:39.162
No problem.

00:01:40.079 --> 00:01:42.290
Well, I still look forward
to working with you.

00:01:43.207 --> 00:01:44.375
Me too.

00:01:44.459 --> 00:01:45.585
Oh, Masumi.

00:01:48.254 --> 00:01:49.297
Happy New Year.

00:01:53.676 --> 00:01:54.802
Happy New Year.

00:02:10.860 --> 00:02:12.070
All right.

00:02:17.617 --> 00:02:18.451
I'M BACK TOGETHER WITH TAIGA!

00:02:18.534 --> 00:02:19.410
IT'S ALL THANK'S TO YOU, OPPA!

00:02:19.494 --> 00:02:20.370
I'LL TREAT YOU A BIG MEAL!
RIGHT, WE CAN SEE AT TANOMI!

00:02:20.453 --> 00:02:21.412
THANK YOU!

00:02:27.543 --> 00:02:28.836
I see.

00:02:31.130 --> 00:02:32.340
Congratulations, Rin.

00:03:36.654 --> 00:03:37.572
Visiting a shrine?

00:03:38.114 --> 00:03:41.075
Yeah, for hatsumode. Want to go together?

00:03:41.659 --> 00:03:44.120
What is "hatsumode"?

00:03:45.163 --> 00:03:48.958
You pray for happiness for the new year.

00:03:49.584 --> 00:03:51.294
I want to go with you.

00:03:51.377 --> 00:03:52.378
What do you think?

00:03:52.462 --> 00:03:53.504
That sounds like fun.

00:03:54.630 --> 00:03:56.257
That's settled then.

00:03:57.759 --> 00:04:01.512
Also, we're having a New Year's party
at Tanomi, so you should come too.

00:04:01.596 --> 00:04:02.638
There will be osechi too.

00:04:03.181 --> 00:04:04.515
- Osechi?
- Yeah.

00:04:04.599 --> 00:04:05.808
I've heard of that before.

00:04:08.978 --> 00:04:12.023
It's a meal you eat
during New Year's, huh?

00:04:13.274 --> 00:04:15.360
It'll be my first time. How exciting.

00:04:25.119 --> 00:04:26.245
What's wrong?

00:04:26.913 --> 00:04:30.166
I'm so happy
that I get to be with you again.

00:04:31.250 --> 00:04:33.836
Me too. I feel the same way.

00:04:33.920 --> 00:04:35.797
- Really?
- Yeah.

00:04:35.880 --> 00:04:37.048
Jinjja?

00:04:38.091 --> 00:04:39.133
Jinjja.

00:04:44.305 --> 00:04:45.515
Here you go.

00:04:47.392 --> 00:04:48.476
Here you go.

00:04:49.018 --> 00:04:50.436
All right.

00:04:50.520 --> 00:04:52.230
Osechi is so cute.

00:04:52.772 --> 00:04:54.190
Taiga and I made it together.

00:04:54.273 --> 00:04:55.775
It takes a lot of time and energy.

00:04:56.651 --> 00:04:59.195
It's like a work of art.
You really are a pro, huh?

00:05:00.113 --> 00:05:01.989
All right, eat up.

00:05:03.241 --> 00:05:04.909
Rin, you're not going back to Korea?

00:05:10.498 --> 00:05:12.208
Yeah…

00:05:13.209 --> 00:05:15.670
I'll be staying in Japan for now.

00:05:17.296 --> 00:05:20.883
That's not what I meant.
I was talking about the New Year's break.

00:05:21.843 --> 00:05:25.805
Oh, but I guess you celebrate
the Lunar New Year in Korea, right?

00:05:25.888 --> 00:05:26.931
Yes.

00:05:28.224 --> 00:05:29.559
What about you, Shige?

00:05:29.642 --> 00:05:30.518
Yeah…

00:05:30.601 --> 00:05:34.439
My sister is in the hospital,
so nobody will be home anyway.

00:05:34.522 --> 00:05:37.441
So I just delivered osechi
to her as a gift.

00:05:37.525 --> 00:05:38.526
I see.

00:05:39.360 --> 00:05:41.237
Anyway, go ahead and eat.

00:05:42.029 --> 00:05:43.030
Thanks for the food.

00:05:43.114 --> 00:05:44.699
Thanks for the food.

00:05:53.374 --> 00:05:55.418
These black soybeans are delicious.

00:05:56.127 --> 00:05:57.587
The black soybeans

00:05:57.670 --> 00:06:01.883
symbolize the desire to work
diligently throughout the new year.

00:06:01.966 --> 00:06:05.052
- Each osechi dish symbolizes something?
- Yes.

00:06:05.678 --> 00:06:09.265
Lotus roots
have holes that you can see through,

00:06:09.348 --> 00:06:11.767
so they symbolize having a bright future.

00:06:11.851 --> 00:06:13.436
How interesting.

00:06:17.648 --> 00:06:19.025
Happy New Year.

00:06:19.108 --> 00:06:20.401
- Happy New Year.
- Happy New Year.

00:06:20.484 --> 00:06:22.195
Here, Noa, have a seat.

00:06:22.278 --> 00:06:23.613
Thanks.

00:06:23.696 --> 00:06:26.908
All right. Happy New Year.

00:06:26.991 --> 00:06:29.827
I look forward
to spending this New Year with you.

00:06:30.369 --> 00:06:31.787
- Thank you.
- You're welcome.

00:06:32.371 --> 00:06:34.332
Eat the osechi with your mom.

00:06:34.415 --> 00:06:36.459
Thank you so much, Shige.

00:06:37.543 --> 00:06:39.003
I got my New Year's money.

00:06:39.086 --> 00:06:40.713
Good for you, Noa.

00:06:43.174 --> 00:06:44.550
New Year's is the best.

00:06:44.634 --> 00:06:45.635
Yeah.

00:06:46.594 --> 00:06:50.014
Speaking of which, do they give out money
on New Year's in Korea too?

00:06:50.598 --> 00:06:54.227
In Korea, if you do a "sebae" like this,
you get "don,"

00:06:54.310 --> 00:06:55.269
which means money.

00:06:55.353 --> 00:06:56.896
And so, we call it "sebaetdon."

00:06:58.231 --> 00:06:59.607
Sebaetdon?

00:07:00.233 --> 00:07:01.776
- Yeah, sebaetdon.
- Interesting.

00:07:02.360 --> 00:07:06.072
I like that system.
Maybe I should go around doing sebae?

00:07:06.155 --> 00:07:08.616
All you have been talking about is money.

00:07:08.699 --> 00:07:11.619
Well, I'm always the one
giving money to others.

00:07:11.702 --> 00:07:15.706
I don't get New Year's money
from my parents or my boyfriend.

00:07:15.790 --> 00:07:17.792
{\an8}You've got to be kidding!

00:07:18.459 --> 00:07:20.753
40,000 just in one morning?

00:07:22.421 --> 00:07:25.633
Akinori, we're getting lunch.
Want to come?

00:07:26.509 --> 00:07:28.844
I'll keep at it.

00:07:30.429 --> 00:07:33.182
You should take a breather
and start fresh.

00:07:34.308 --> 00:07:36.978
Plus, I want to let you in on a nice deal.

00:07:40.940 --> 00:07:44.235
Investment?
So that really is profitable, huh?

00:07:44.318 --> 00:07:45.570
It's a pretty sweet deal.

00:07:46.362 --> 00:07:49.907
You can expect 200,000 a month
in dividends.

00:07:49.991 --> 00:07:51.492
It's a solid investment.

00:07:51.576 --> 00:07:52.827
200,000 a month?

00:07:53.786 --> 00:07:55.246
That sounds like a dream.

00:07:55.830 --> 00:07:57.873
We can make bank through investments

00:07:58.624 --> 00:07:59.667
and relax and have fun.

00:08:05.214 --> 00:08:06.465
But…

00:08:07.466 --> 00:08:10.595
I need 500,000 to start, huh?

00:08:14.265 --> 00:08:16.350
If you're going to hesitate, back out.

00:08:16.434 --> 00:08:19.562
Do you understand how lucky you are
that Zaki is letting you in on this?

00:08:19.645 --> 00:08:22.690
No, no! I'm really grateful! I'm sorry.

00:08:25.234 --> 00:08:26.235
Um…

00:08:27.695 --> 00:08:30.197
When do I need the money by,
in order to join?

00:08:32.074 --> 00:08:35.036
The cutoff
is at the beginning of next week,

00:08:35.119 --> 00:08:38.039
so three days is all I can wait.

00:08:39.707 --> 00:08:41.042
Three days?

00:08:48.090 --> 00:08:50.301
This is the best. It's so delicious.

00:08:50.384 --> 00:08:52.803
Noa, you're drinking too fast.

00:08:52.887 --> 00:08:54.138
It's fine.

00:08:54.221 --> 00:08:56.265
I'm so happy.

00:08:57.767 --> 00:09:00.227
This year is looking promising.

00:09:01.145 --> 00:09:02.521
You're drinking too much.

00:09:03.189 --> 00:09:04.023
Shut up.

00:09:04.106 --> 00:09:09.320
HAPPY NEW YEAR

00:09:09.403 --> 00:09:11.530
- Hey, Noa!
- Yes?

00:09:11.614 --> 00:09:13.991
You forgot your osechi.

00:09:14.533 --> 00:09:16.243
- Sorry. Thank you.
- There.

00:09:16.327 --> 00:09:17.870
- Thank you.
- Get home safe.

00:09:17.953 --> 00:09:18.788
- Okay.
- Bye.

00:09:18.871 --> 00:09:20.414
- Bye, everyone.
- Bye.

00:09:22.458 --> 00:09:23.793
We'll get going too.

00:09:23.876 --> 00:09:24.710
Okay.

00:09:24.794 --> 00:09:26.462
Thank you for the food, Shige.

00:09:26.545 --> 00:09:28.422
You're welcome. Go have fun.

00:09:37.181 --> 00:09:38.391
What?

00:09:41.686 --> 00:09:44.397
This is getting pretty old.

00:09:44.480 --> 00:09:49.527
‪TANOMI

00:09:49.610 --> 00:09:52.780
{\an8}TOJO GENERAL HOSPITAL

00:09:59.453 --> 00:10:01.872
I come to this shrine every New Year's.

00:10:02.415 --> 00:10:03.666
{\an8}Oh really?

00:10:03.749 --> 00:10:04.709
{\an8}Yeah.

00:10:04.792 --> 00:10:07.628
{\an8}HATSUMODE

00:10:11.924 --> 00:10:14.176
- Here you go.
- Thanks.

00:10:14.760 --> 00:10:16.053
Put it in here.

00:10:16.762 --> 00:10:18.931
Here we go. Ready…

00:10:31.652 --> 00:10:35.906
I pray that I can be true to myself

00:10:35.990 --> 00:10:38.826
and be with Taiga forever.

00:10:41.078 --> 00:10:44.331
I pray that I can be with Rin forever.

00:10:44.874 --> 00:10:47.793
Also, I pray that things work out well

00:10:47.877 --> 00:10:50.296
regarding my work and my goals.

00:10:50.379 --> 00:10:51.839
Also, I pray that

00:10:52.381 --> 00:10:56.302
my family, Rin, Rin's family,
and the people around me

00:10:56.385 --> 00:10:59.305
all enjoy good health
and live a happy life.

00:10:59.847 --> 00:11:02.600
I'm sorry for asking for so many things.

00:11:02.683 --> 00:11:05.728
Oh, but also, I pray that
everything goes smoothly.

00:11:05.811 --> 00:11:09.523
Thank you very much!
My name is Hase Taiga!

00:11:23.537 --> 00:11:26.207
I'm sorry. I asked for a lot of things.

00:11:27.124 --> 00:11:28.501
{\an8}FORTUNE

00:11:28.584 --> 00:11:30.669
{\an8}HATSUMODE

00:11:30.753 --> 00:11:32.838
{\an8}- I'll pick mine now.
- Okay.

00:11:40.095 --> 00:11:41.805
- Ready…
- Ready…

00:11:45.893 --> 00:11:47.102
How mediocre.

00:11:47.186 --> 00:11:48.562
Blessings…

00:11:48.646 --> 00:11:49.522
Huh?

00:11:49.605 --> 00:11:50.940
It says I get blessings.

00:11:52.066 --> 00:11:55.027
That's better than me.
What does it say underneath?

00:11:56.779 --> 00:11:58.197
Give me a second…

00:12:02.493 --> 00:12:04.787
YOUR FORTUNE

00:12:04.870 --> 00:12:09.166
It says that my wishes will come true.

00:12:10.167 --> 00:12:11.293
That's great!

00:12:11.794 --> 00:12:13.045
Let me see.

00:12:13.128 --> 00:12:14.255
No.

00:12:14.338 --> 00:12:15.714
Why not?

00:12:15.798 --> 00:12:18.384
I'll take my time and read it
when I'm alone.

00:12:18.467 --> 00:12:20.511
Let's read it together now.

00:12:20.594 --> 00:12:21.512
- Come on!
- No.

00:12:21.595 --> 00:12:23.097
- Just a little.
- No!

00:12:23.180 --> 00:12:24.848
Just the first part.

00:12:27.851 --> 00:12:29.144
INTERNSHIP PROGRAM

00:12:39.405 --> 00:12:41.323
Hey!

00:12:41.407 --> 00:12:44.577
Taiga, I think it's time for a break.

00:12:45.119 --> 00:12:47.621
Okay. In a second.

00:12:48.664 --> 00:12:50.416
You're so studious, Taiga.

00:12:51.458 --> 00:12:54.044
Let's take a break already.

00:12:54.837 --> 00:12:57.131
Yeah… Just a second.

00:12:58.549 --> 00:13:00.884
Let's take a break.

00:13:01.427 --> 00:13:02.595
Hey, come on.

00:13:03.887 --> 00:13:05.014
- Hey!
- A break.

00:13:05.097 --> 00:13:06.223
Okay!

00:13:06.307 --> 00:13:07.725
- Let's take a break.
- Okay.

00:13:11.854 --> 00:13:15.858
Hey, you were so focused,
but what were you doing?

00:13:16.400 --> 00:13:19.320
Right now, I was looking at this.

00:13:20.362 --> 00:13:21.196
NEO MEAL JAPAN
REAL NUTRITION IN MEALS FOR ATHLETES

00:13:21.280 --> 00:13:24.116
"Meals for athletes…"

00:13:25.909 --> 00:13:29.830
It's a job that supports athletes
through food.

00:13:31.206 --> 00:13:34.501
I think I finally have an idea
of what my dream is.

00:13:35.085 --> 00:13:37.046
Although it took time to get here.

00:13:38.464 --> 00:13:40.049
Good for you, Taiga.

00:13:41.884 --> 00:13:43.427
It's all thanks to you.

00:13:45.846 --> 00:13:47.056
And so…

00:13:51.268 --> 00:13:52.936
I have something important to talk about.

00:13:55.272 --> 00:13:58.609
How long will your internship last?

00:14:01.070 --> 00:14:04.073
It'll end before I graduate.

00:14:04.156 --> 00:14:06.033
What will you do after that?

00:14:06.742 --> 00:14:09.453
I still don't know for sure.

00:14:11.080 --> 00:14:12.373
You know,

00:14:13.290 --> 00:14:17.002
I don't think it's right
to avoid this topic.

00:14:18.420 --> 00:14:22.007
So I want to face this issue properly.

00:14:24.635 --> 00:14:28.597
Once you graduate,
you have to return to Korea, right?

00:14:29.640 --> 00:14:31.392
You don't have a work visa, after all.

00:14:33.936 --> 00:14:36.605
Yeah, at this rate,
that's what will happen.

00:14:37.189 --> 00:14:38.440
Right…

00:14:39.149 --> 00:14:41.819
Unless you get hired
by a Japanese company,

00:14:42.528 --> 00:14:44.029
you have to go back.

00:14:44.530 --> 00:14:45.614
On top of that,

00:14:46.240 --> 00:14:49.493
you have to decide what you
want to become in the future,

00:14:49.576 --> 00:14:51.495
and work toward that goal,

00:14:52.705 --> 00:14:56.417
and think about whether or not
to stay with me.

00:14:57.459 --> 00:14:59.294
I'm sorry that I wasn't able

00:14:59.837 --> 00:15:02.214
to understand something so obvious.

00:15:03.090 --> 00:15:04.049
Don't worry.

00:15:06.093 --> 00:15:08.220
You've always been so kind to me.

00:15:10.806 --> 00:15:14.059
I still don't fully know
all of the difficulties you face.

00:15:15.602 --> 00:15:16.895
But I…

00:15:18.230 --> 00:15:22.234
want to stay with you
even after you graduate.

00:15:24.653 --> 00:15:25.779
So…

00:15:26.572 --> 00:15:28.824
I will do what I can, to make that happen.

00:15:29.742 --> 00:15:31.827
I'll make sure that we can
see each other regularly,

00:15:32.327 --> 00:15:34.121
no matter what you decide to do.

00:15:35.914 --> 00:15:38.625
To do that,
I'll learn to stand on my own two feet,

00:15:39.501 --> 00:15:41.003
even while chasing my dream.

00:15:44.923 --> 00:15:46.008
Taiga…

00:15:49.094 --> 00:15:50.596
In the end,

00:15:51.263 --> 00:15:53.724
I'm saying the same thing as before,
aren't I?

00:15:54.975 --> 00:15:58.771
I still don't have the guts to tell you
to stay in Japan.

00:15:59.313 --> 00:16:00.814
- But--
- It's not the same.

00:16:02.274 --> 00:16:03.484
It's totally different.

00:16:08.322 --> 00:16:09.823
I'm really happy.

00:16:10.866 --> 00:16:13.827
I want to be with you too.

00:16:16.246 --> 00:16:17.414
You do?

00:16:18.749 --> 00:16:22.252
I only have a little bit of time left,
but I'll do what I can.

00:16:29.510 --> 00:16:31.345
Noa, how are things with dongsaeng?

00:16:33.263 --> 00:16:34.348
Why all of a sudden?

00:16:35.724 --> 00:16:39.311
The thing is, he just contacted me
and said, "Let's go eat."

00:16:39.853 --> 00:16:41.438
What? I don't know about this.

00:16:41.522 --> 00:16:42.648
Go eat where?

00:16:43.607 --> 00:16:46.860
He said he wants to talk to me
about his future.

00:16:48.070 --> 00:16:49.571
Future?

00:16:50.531 --> 00:16:51.865
Akinori said that?

00:16:52.574 --> 00:16:53.742
Yes.

00:16:53.826 --> 00:16:56.120
It seems he is seriously

00:16:56.203 --> 00:16:58.247
thinking about a future with you.

00:17:01.166 --> 00:17:02.292
I see…

00:17:04.962 --> 00:17:06.463
As if!

00:17:06.547 --> 00:17:09.174
That was close! I almost fell for it.

00:17:12.302 --> 00:17:13.887
That was close…

00:17:26.024 --> 00:17:27.776
Ms. Park, do you have a moment?

00:17:28.610 --> 00:17:29.820
Yes?

00:17:29.903 --> 00:17:34.241
We're about to have a meeting
with a client, but I want you to join.

00:17:34.992 --> 00:17:37.286
- Me?
- Yes.

00:17:37.369 --> 00:17:41.623
Our client this time is
a Japanese subsidiary of a Korean company.

00:17:41.707 --> 00:17:43.125
I thought it's a good opportunity.

00:17:44.334 --> 00:17:46.587
- I would love to.
- Yeah?

00:17:47.212 --> 00:17:51.216
All that is left to discuss
is how to advertise the product.

00:17:51.842 --> 00:17:54.595
Do you have any requests
regarding the creative aspect?

00:17:54.678 --> 00:17:58.473
Yes, upon entering the Japanese market,
we would like to create

00:17:58.557 --> 00:18:01.560
a character IP that will catch
the attention of our target demographic.

00:18:01.643 --> 00:18:04.188
I see. Understood.

00:18:04.855 --> 00:18:06.440
Which means,

00:18:06.523 --> 00:18:09.359
the creative department
and illustrators will team up.

00:18:09.443 --> 00:18:10.652
How about

00:18:11.195 --> 00:18:15.407
we hold a contest within our company,
and choose from there?

00:18:15.991 --> 00:18:19.328
That sounds great. Let's go with that.

00:18:19.953 --> 00:18:21.663
Well then, thank you for your time.

00:18:21.747 --> 00:18:23.373
Thank you very much.

00:18:24.541 --> 00:18:25.834
- Good bye.
- Good bye.

00:18:31.715 --> 00:18:33.050
‪All right.

00:18:35.802 --> 00:18:37.429
- Ms. Hoshiumi.
- Yes?

00:18:39.932 --> 00:18:43.894
May I take part in the contest too?

00:18:45.729 --> 00:18:46.939
Well, of course.

00:18:47.731 --> 00:18:51.109
I'm looking for an open, fun idea.

00:18:52.778 --> 00:18:54.196
Thank you very much!

00:18:54.279 --> 00:18:55.739
You know,

00:18:55.822 --> 00:18:58.408
it's so nice that you
seized that opportunity yourself.

00:18:59.076 --> 00:19:00.702
Do your best.

00:19:02.412 --> 00:19:04.164
Yeah, thank you.

00:19:07.793 --> 00:19:10.212
I must say, your future looks so bright.

00:19:10.295 --> 00:19:14.007
It's a little blinding for me.
It's the beauty of youth.

00:19:14.675 --> 00:19:17.261
You and I are the same age.

00:19:17.344 --> 00:19:18.720
I know, but still.

00:19:19.388 --> 00:19:22.140
My life is going to stay the same forever.

00:19:23.058 --> 00:19:24.768
It's not going to change.

00:19:29.439 --> 00:19:32.901
Don't get the wrong idea.
I'm enjoying my life the way it is.

00:19:36.071 --> 00:19:38.323
I don't need my dreams to come true.

00:19:40.659 --> 00:19:42.619
Just working at this hotel,

00:19:43.328 --> 00:19:46.164
and watching guests
from all over the world

00:19:46.248 --> 00:19:50.168
makes me feel like I'm living overseas
and it's exciting.

00:19:50.961 --> 00:19:52.421
That's enough for me.

00:19:54.464 --> 00:19:57.884
Have you ever thought about
actually going overseas?

00:19:57.968 --> 00:19:59.678
There's no way I can.

00:20:00.637 --> 00:20:04.266
Why? I know you're studying English.

00:20:04.808 --> 00:20:07.185
You're working and have money too.

00:20:07.728 --> 00:20:11.315
No matter how much I make,
my mother and boyfriend use it all up.

00:20:11.398 --> 00:20:14.568
So it's not realistic.
You and I are different.

00:20:17.279 --> 00:20:19.698
If you really want to go overseas,

00:20:19.781 --> 00:20:22.284
just think about what you need to do
to make it happen.

00:20:23.702 --> 00:20:26.872
Must be nice to have been
raised in a privileged environment.

00:20:26.955 --> 00:20:29.958
Everyone should become
who they want to be.

00:20:30.042 --> 00:20:33.003
I'll think about it with you.
Let's share ideas. Okay?

00:20:34.921 --> 00:20:38.091
You are such a crazy princess.

00:20:39.051 --> 00:20:41.636
What the heck? Are you making fun of me?

00:20:42.429 --> 00:20:43.472
It's a compliment.

00:20:44.097 --> 00:20:45.974
I like that about you.

00:20:48.310 --> 00:20:50.020
- Let's hurry up and eat.
- Okay.

00:20:50.520 --> 00:20:51.355
TANOMI

00:20:51.438 --> 00:20:52.689
Closing Tanomi?

00:20:52.773 --> 00:20:53.648
Yeah.

00:20:53.732 --> 00:20:55.400
Nothing is official yet.

00:20:56.401 --> 00:20:59.488
I'm just saying that it's a possibility
we have to consider.

00:21:00.739 --> 00:21:02.491
Did something happen?

00:21:03.116 --> 00:21:06.912
I got a call from the hospital
saying my sister's condition isn't good.

00:21:07.496 --> 00:21:09.831
It can't be helped, you know?

00:21:11.666 --> 00:21:14.669
Come on, don't look so depressed.

00:21:14.753 --> 00:21:17.130
It's not like we're closing this instant.

00:21:20.425 --> 00:21:21.426
But…

00:21:22.344 --> 00:21:23.929
I'm sorry for making you worry.

00:21:24.471 --> 00:21:26.848
But what will be, will be.

00:21:30.018 --> 00:21:31.478
This may sound cliché,

00:21:32.229 --> 00:21:37.067
but you really can't take
what you have for granted.

00:21:37.609 --> 00:21:39.611
The older I get, the more I feel that way.

00:21:48.120 --> 00:21:49.329
I see.

00:21:49.871 --> 00:21:52.207
Thank you for sharing your thoughts.

00:21:52.290 --> 00:21:53.333
So you are looking

00:21:53.875 --> 00:21:57.003
for a job where you can
support athletes with your cooking?

00:21:57.087 --> 00:21:58.338
Yes.

00:21:59.131 --> 00:22:00.215
I…

00:22:00.966 --> 00:22:04.219
have been turning my eyes away
from the defeat

00:22:04.302 --> 00:22:06.346
I experienced in track
during my college days.

00:22:07.431 --> 00:22:09.057
I started cooking

00:22:09.683 --> 00:22:11.560
because I couldn't run as an athlete,

00:22:12.394 --> 00:22:14.604
and I had no other choice.

00:22:16.982 --> 00:22:18.066
But now,

00:22:19.192 --> 00:22:22.028
I genuinely feel a sense of accomplishment

00:22:22.946 --> 00:22:26.408
from this job,
where I can cook for others.

00:22:26.491 --> 00:22:27.868
Is that right?

00:22:28.451 --> 00:22:29.661
That's why

00:22:30.287 --> 00:22:33.415
I believe I can
make even better use of myself,

00:22:33.957 --> 00:22:36.459
if I can find a career
in making food for athletes.

00:22:36.543 --> 00:22:37.586
I see.

00:22:38.712 --> 00:22:41.506
And so, I did a lot of research

00:22:41.590 --> 00:22:44.676
and found that it takes four years
to become a registered dietitian.

00:22:45.260 --> 00:22:49.347
And even after that,
I need work experience to do anything…

00:22:49.890 --> 00:22:51.933
But you are in a hurry, right?

00:22:52.851 --> 00:22:53.935
Yes.

00:22:54.603 --> 00:22:56.855
I'd like to start working
as soon as possible.

00:23:00.942 --> 00:23:03.737
In that case,
you should get right into it.

00:23:05.447 --> 00:23:06.323
Huh?

00:23:07.741 --> 00:23:09.784
You can work for places like

00:23:10.368 --> 00:23:13.205
college dorms and company teams
with just a registration.

00:23:14.372 --> 00:23:15.707
Is that right?

00:23:16.583 --> 00:23:19.002
Why don't you just try it out?

00:23:20.378 --> 00:23:22.380
You can gain experience while working,

00:23:23.215 --> 00:23:25.258
and aim to become a sports dietitian.

00:23:26.134 --> 00:23:27.844
That's a valid option.

00:23:32.349 --> 00:23:33.516
Look.

00:23:34.851 --> 00:23:36.061
This one,

00:23:37.687 --> 00:23:38.772
and this one.

00:23:39.356 --> 00:23:41.524
They look pretty good, don't they?

00:23:43.068 --> 00:23:44.819
Well, doesn't someone look happy…

00:23:45.445 --> 00:23:46.947
You're really not coming back?

00:23:48.073 --> 00:23:49.199
I'm not.

00:23:49.282 --> 00:23:50.951
You're an idiot.

00:23:51.701 --> 00:23:55.372
Even if you can find a job in Japan,

00:23:55.455 --> 00:23:58.667
what if you break up in six months
or a year?

00:23:58.750 --> 00:24:00.210
You really won't regret this?

00:24:01.962 --> 00:24:03.004
I won't.

00:24:04.256 --> 00:24:08.927
Taiga treats me well,
so I want to stay with him.

00:24:09.594 --> 00:24:13.098
Jeez, you can gush about your boyfriend
all you want,

00:24:13.181 --> 00:24:15.225
but understand that I'm worried about you.

00:24:15.308 --> 00:24:16.685
Thank you.

00:24:16.768 --> 00:24:19.187
But I don't want to ignore
the way I'm feeling right now.

00:24:19.271 --> 00:24:22.941
Worrying about it
won't solve anything anyway.

00:24:23.024 --> 00:24:25.694
That might be right, but…

00:24:27.279 --> 00:24:29.906
You really don't need to worry.

00:24:29.990 --> 00:24:31.366
We won't break up.

00:24:33.118 --> 00:24:34.035
Please!

00:24:36.037 --> 00:24:38.248
So you just wanted money, huh?

00:24:39.833 --> 00:24:41.167
I'm sorry, hyeongnim.

00:24:42.794 --> 00:24:47.048
But I really want to pay
for Noa's mom's surgery.

00:24:48.883 --> 00:24:49.884
But…

00:24:51.678 --> 00:24:53.054
I have no money on hand.

00:24:54.306 --> 00:24:55.348
So…

00:24:56.308 --> 00:24:58.560
Please lend me some money.
I'll give it right back!

00:24:59.728 --> 00:25:02.022
Does Noa know about this?

00:25:03.023 --> 00:25:04.274
I'm keeping it a secret.

00:25:04.774 --> 00:25:06.776
I don't want her to feel bad about it.

00:25:13.450 --> 00:25:15.285
I will secretly work and pay you back.

00:25:15.368 --> 00:25:18.496
So please! Help cure Noa's mom's sickness!

00:25:18.580 --> 00:25:21.207
Hyeongnim, you're the only one I can ask!
Please!

00:25:24.836 --> 00:25:30.091
{\an8}Forty-six, forty-seven, forty-eight,
forty-nine, fifty.

00:25:31.468 --> 00:25:32.719
It's all here.

00:25:33.386 --> 00:25:34.220
Okay.

00:25:34.304 --> 00:25:36.931
- All right then, I'll hold onto this.
- Okay.

00:25:37.432 --> 00:25:38.558
Um…

00:25:38.641 --> 00:25:41.686
With this,
I can definitely get the dividend, right?

00:25:42.228 --> 00:25:43.855
Of course!

00:25:43.938 --> 00:25:44.939
Good job.

00:25:46.066 --> 00:25:47.359
I'm so relieved!

00:25:47.442 --> 00:25:49.694
I worked really hard collecting
this money.

00:25:49.778 --> 00:25:51.946
I even cried
to my girlfriend's friends for help.

00:25:52.489 --> 00:25:54.532
You're brave, Akinori!

00:25:55.450 --> 00:25:58.495
Here, this is your first dividend.

00:25:58.578 --> 00:25:59.662
Wow, really?

00:26:00.580 --> 00:26:02.707
You'd better be grateful.

00:26:03.333 --> 00:26:05.668
This is what you'll be getting
every month.

00:26:05.752 --> 00:26:07.796
200,000 a month, huh?

00:26:07.879 --> 00:26:11.132
This is awesome! Amazing!

00:26:11.216 --> 00:26:13.885
In three months,
you will have made a profit of 100,000.

00:26:13.968 --> 00:26:16.137
From there, you'll just keep
receiving 200,000 a month.

00:26:18.139 --> 00:26:21.309
Zaki! Thank you for letting me in on this!

00:26:21.393 --> 00:26:23.144
Don't worry about it!

00:26:23.228 --> 00:26:25.480
I want my friends to live a good life.

00:26:27.107 --> 00:26:28.149
Thanks!

00:26:28.900 --> 00:26:31.486
- All right, then! I'll be leaving now!
- See you.

00:26:31.569 --> 00:26:32.737
Yes!

00:26:34.239 --> 00:26:35.407
Yes!

00:26:36.491 --> 00:26:37.700
What an idiot.

00:26:43.331 --> 00:26:44.582
Excuse me.

00:26:44.666 --> 00:26:47.836
I'm Hase. I called earlier.
I'm here to receive a pamphlet.

00:26:47.919 --> 00:26:49.462
One moment please.

00:27:27.584 --> 00:27:29.419
- This smells amazing.
- Sorry to make you wait.

00:27:29.502 --> 00:27:30.378
Hey.

00:27:33.006 --> 00:27:34.382
You bought more things?

00:27:34.924 --> 00:27:35.925
Yeah.

00:27:36.634 --> 00:27:38.636
What do you think? Isn't it cool?

00:27:40.221 --> 00:27:41.473
Yeah, sure.

00:27:47.520 --> 00:27:48.354
Here.

00:27:48.438 --> 00:27:49.564
Thank you for everything.

00:27:50.106 --> 00:27:50.982
Huh?

00:27:53.359 --> 00:27:55.737
You seem to be living large these days.

00:27:56.279 --> 00:27:57.906
Where did you get this money?

00:27:57.989 --> 00:28:00.992
I'm earning it through investments.

00:28:02.577 --> 00:28:05.330
Investment?
Don't you need money to invest first?

00:28:05.413 --> 00:28:06.498
Where did you get that?

00:28:06.581 --> 00:28:07.999
I borrowed it.

00:28:08.082 --> 00:28:09.959
- From who?
- A friend.

00:28:10.043 --> 00:28:11.336
Which friend?

00:28:12.045 --> 00:28:14.130
Just a friend.

00:28:17.967 --> 00:28:19.928
Tell me who you borrowed it from.

00:28:20.011 --> 00:28:21.137
Huh?

00:28:21.888 --> 00:28:24.807
- Who cares about that?
- Just tell me!

00:28:26.601 --> 00:28:28.603
Why are you all mad?

00:28:29.729 --> 00:28:33.858
I know I'm always troubling you,
so this time I got the money myself.

00:28:34.567 --> 00:28:36.361
- Why can't you be happy--
- I would rather

00:28:36.444 --> 00:28:37.403
you bother me than other people!

00:28:37.487 --> 00:28:38.613
Just tell me!

00:28:40.156 --> 00:28:41.366
I'm sorry.

00:28:41.449 --> 00:28:42.575
Sorry about that.

00:28:43.618 --> 00:28:46.621
Hey, don't get so mad!

00:28:50.124 --> 00:28:52.168
It was Jun-ho.

00:28:53.837 --> 00:28:56.923
- You really--
- I can pay him back right away.

00:28:57.423 --> 00:29:01.177
I already got my 200,000 dividend
and I don't need to pay anymore.

00:29:01.261 --> 00:29:02.554
Now I just get 200,000 every month--

00:29:02.637 --> 00:29:05.306
Obviously that's too good to be true!
Are you an idiot?!

00:29:05.390 --> 00:29:06.850
It's true!

00:29:09.269 --> 00:29:11.938
I'll be getting a steady income.

00:29:12.605 --> 00:29:13.648
Then,

00:29:14.190 --> 00:29:16.651
we'll be able to rent a place
and live together.

00:29:20.029 --> 00:29:22.490
Have a little faith in me, will you?

00:29:29.956 --> 00:29:31.708
Let's go apologize to Jun-ho.

00:29:34.085 --> 00:29:35.837
- What?
- I said, let's go!

00:29:45.430 --> 00:29:46.890
I'm really sorry.

00:29:47.807 --> 00:29:48.850
Hyeongnim…

00:29:50.101 --> 00:29:51.394
I'm sorry.

00:29:52.228 --> 00:29:55.398
- I didn't mean to trick you--
- This isn't your time to make excuses.

00:29:56.733 --> 00:29:58.276
We're only here to apologize.

00:29:58.359 --> 00:29:59.861
I was going to return it double.

00:29:59.944 --> 00:30:02.363
- But--
- It's too good to be true.

00:30:02.447 --> 00:30:03.781
You're so stupid.

00:30:04.490 --> 00:30:06.159
I said, I'm sorry.

00:30:06.701 --> 00:30:08.077
How stupid can you be?

00:30:09.329 --> 00:30:10.997
It's almost sad.

00:30:13.458 --> 00:30:15.752
I knew you were stupid,
but this is a new low.

00:30:15.835 --> 00:30:17.587
Stop calling me stupid.

00:30:17.670 --> 00:30:20.840
- I wanted to change too, you know?
- Then why did you borrow money?

00:30:20.924 --> 00:30:22.592
You need money to change!

00:30:22.675 --> 00:30:24.093
Just apologize already!

00:30:24.177 --> 00:30:25.303
Enough!

00:30:27.430 --> 00:30:28.389
Dongsaeng,

00:30:29.307 --> 00:30:30.934
I lent you money

00:30:31.643 --> 00:30:33.728
because I trusted you as a person.

00:30:38.900 --> 00:30:40.485
This is Noa's money, isn't it?

00:30:42.070 --> 00:30:43.363
Then I can't accept it.

00:30:46.032 --> 00:30:47.075
You need to pay me yourself.

00:30:48.451 --> 00:30:49.744
I trust you.

00:31:04.384 --> 00:31:07.470
That kind of attitude
is the most annoying.

00:31:09.347 --> 00:31:10.390
Huh?

00:31:12.225 --> 00:31:13.685
Are you serious?

00:31:15.019 --> 00:31:17.730
Do you not understand
how kind he is being?

00:31:17.814 --> 00:31:21.192
You guys just look down on me, that's all.

00:31:22.944 --> 00:31:26.114
You trusted me of your own will,
and now you're disappointed.

00:31:27.657 --> 00:31:29.200
It's so annoying.

00:31:30.368 --> 00:31:32.578
Hey… Hey!

00:31:32.662 --> 00:31:35.164
Move. Hey…

00:31:39.335 --> 00:31:40.378
Please…

00:31:44.090 --> 00:31:45.216
Apologize.

00:32:09.991 --> 00:32:11.409
I'm sorry, Jun-ho.

00:32:16.706 --> 00:32:17.832
This is…

00:32:19.584 --> 00:32:20.460
too much…

00:32:37.643 --> 00:32:39.020
You don't need to worry.

00:32:43.775 --> 00:32:44.776
That…

00:32:47.445 --> 00:32:48.738
Will you please accept it?

00:32:53.284 --> 00:32:55.036
I lent money to him, not you.

00:33:03.169 --> 00:33:07.090
So what are you going to do
about your boyfriend?

00:33:24.357 --> 00:33:25.983
I guess it's over.

00:33:27.944 --> 00:33:29.946
There's no future with him.

00:33:34.909 --> 00:33:35.952
Noa…

00:33:37.620 --> 00:33:38.913
Thank you.

00:33:42.458 --> 00:33:43.668
You know how…

00:33:45.419 --> 00:33:46.879
you told me before…

00:33:49.340 --> 00:33:51.008
that I should become who I want to be?

00:33:52.760 --> 00:33:53.845
Yeah.

00:34:03.646 --> 00:34:06.232
If I stay with him,
I don't think I'll ever change.

00:34:11.612 --> 00:34:12.947
I see.

00:34:24.167 --> 00:34:25.209
Rin…

00:34:29.630 --> 00:34:30.798
I can do this, right?

00:34:35.595 --> 00:34:38.389
If that is what you truly wish to do,

00:34:39.223 --> 00:34:43.060
I will support that decision,
no matter what it is.

00:34:53.070 --> 00:34:54.447
Thank you.

00:34:58.451 --> 00:34:59.327
You're so nice…

00:35:12.632 --> 00:35:14.217
I'm sorry about everything.

00:35:15.343 --> 00:35:18.012
It's fine. What's done is done.

00:35:21.474 --> 00:35:22.767
Hey…

00:35:25.019 --> 00:35:28.814
What about all the money
I've borrowed from you?

00:35:30.107 --> 00:35:31.359
It's fine.

00:35:32.735 --> 00:35:34.320
Think of it as settlement money.

00:35:35.529 --> 00:35:38.824
More like, can you even pay me back
if I asked for it?

00:35:47.959 --> 00:35:49.043
I can't.

00:35:49.627 --> 00:35:51.587
Don't corner me like that on our last day.

00:36:02.974 --> 00:36:04.934
You didn't forget anything, right?

00:36:05.017 --> 00:36:06.978
No, I don't think so.

00:36:13.401 --> 00:36:14.485
Bye.

00:36:15.027 --> 00:36:17.280
What? You're not seeing me off?

00:36:17.989 --> 00:36:21.075
Why would I? Don't be a baby.

00:36:24.620 --> 00:36:25.621
Okay.

00:36:33.254 --> 00:36:34.255
Bye.

00:36:36.340 --> 00:36:37.633
Akinori.

00:36:41.470 --> 00:36:42.888
It was fun.

00:36:45.933 --> 00:36:47.935
Living like a bum with you.

00:36:52.023 --> 00:36:53.274
What the heck?

00:37:35.399 --> 00:37:36.650
{\an8}All right…

00:37:39.779 --> 00:37:41.906
{\an8}I sent in a few applications.

00:37:41.989 --> 00:37:44.575
{\an8}But I haven't done an entrance exam
in so long, I'm so nervous.

00:37:45.368 --> 00:37:48.329
{\an8}Maybe I'll go to a shrine
and pray that I get accepted.

00:37:48.871 --> 00:37:50.331
{\an8}You'll be fine, Taiga.

00:37:51.165 --> 00:37:52.708
{\an8}I need to do my best too.

00:37:54.502 --> 00:37:56.170
{\an8}I'll get back to work now.

00:37:56.754 --> 00:37:59.507
{\an8}Oh, sorry. Do your best.

00:38:00.091 --> 00:38:02.426
{\an8}I will. Taiga, you can do it too.

00:38:07.306 --> 00:38:08.808
{\an8}Shrine…

00:38:11.102 --> 00:38:13.604
{\an8}I'll take my time and read it
when I'm alone.

00:38:24.698 --> 00:38:26.409
{\an8}I'll lose something big?

00:38:33.124 --> 00:38:36.502
Going into the advertising industry now?
There's no way you'll succeed!

00:38:36.585 --> 00:38:38.587
You've been suffocating me like that
this whole time.

00:38:38.671 --> 00:38:40.214
{\an8}Can you please translate

00:38:40.798 --> 00:38:43.050
{\an8}what I'm going to say to your mother?

00:38:43.134 --> 00:38:43.968
{\an8}Subtitle translation by: Kiko Morita